+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/PNF> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Andesite lava and basalt lava with subsidiary breccia, mudstone and tuff. Stratified bedrock. Occurs onshore. Deposited during the Aurelucian Stage - to - Burrellian Stage (Ordovician Period) (458.2-452.5 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/PYGA> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Obsolete name. Lava and pyroclastic-rock. Stratified bedrock. Occurs onshore. Deposited during the Abereiddian Stage - to - Caradoc Series (Ordovician Period) (468-449.75 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/RAT> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Tuff. Stratified bedrock. Occurs onshore. Deposited during the Soudleyan Substage (Ordovician Period) (455.167-453.833 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/RPE> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Obsolete name. Stratified bedrock. Occurs onshore. Deposited during the Homerian Age (Silurian Period) (430.6-426.7 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/S17> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Obsolete name. Stratified bedrock. Occurs onshore. Age not entered."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/S234> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Obsolete name. Stratified bedrock. Occurs onshore. Age not entered."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/SAM> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Obsolete name. Calcareous mudstone, conglomerate, mudstone, sandstone and siltstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs onshore. Deposited during the Lochkovian Age - to - Pragian Age (Devonian Period) (419-410.5 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/SCH> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Obsolete name. Sandstone with subsidiary siliciclastic argillaceous rock. Stratified bedrock. Occurs onshore. Deposited during the Pridoli Epoch (Silurian Period) (422.7-419 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/TRB> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Sandstone with subsidiary mudstone and siltstone and trace breccia, calcrete and ferricrete. Stratified bedrock. Occurs onshore. Deposited during the Gorstian Age (Silurian Period) (426.7-425 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/UMG> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Obsolete name. Conglomerate, mudstone and sandstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs onshore. Deposited during the Pragian Age (Devonian Period) (412.4-410.5 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/UND> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Obsolete name. Siltstone and silty mudstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs onshore. Deposited during the Ludfordian Age (Silurian Period) (425-422.7 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/USB> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Obsolete name. Stratified bedrock. Occurs onshore. Deposited during the Llandovery Epoch (Silurian Period) (443.1-432.9 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/WIL> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Calcareous sandstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs onshore. Deposited during the Cautleyan Stage (Ordovician Period) (449.25-448.75 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/WTA> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Conglomerate, mudstone and sandstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs onshore. Deposited during the Famennian Age (Devonian Period) - to - Tournaisian Age (Carboniferous Period) (371.1-346.7 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/YFS> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Obsolete name. Sandstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs onshore. Deposited during the Famennian Age (Devonian Period) (371.1-359.3 Ma BP)."@en .
